description.narrative: By October 2019, there was an increase of 9,940 additional persons that have accessed sustainable drinking water services through installation of manually drilled boreholes fitted with hand pumps. Additional 65,864 persons (against the annual target of 97,500, or 68% of the target) gained access to basic sanitation services. The same number of people have adopted the practice of hand washing with soap. The above results were registered in areas with high vulnerability for children in six hard to reach counties in south east and northwest Liberia and Montserrado county. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
